      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Brown_25358_1841-04_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1841-04-14"/>Wednesday, Apr. 14<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                  <lb/>
                    1841<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                            Dear Sir, 
                        </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am extremely obliged<lb/>
                    your messenger is in such<lb/>
                    a hurry for my answer<lb/>
                    that I can neither say more<lb/>
                    nor less - Except that<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">Mr. Wilson</persName> will I am sure<lb/>
                    be eager to interest himself<lb/>
                    as you desire for <unclear>Carter</unclear>-<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>My dear sister, <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                  <lb/>
                    Wilson</persName> has been <add>very ill</add> &amp; is but<lb/>
                    just recovering from a <choice>
                  <orig>dan-<lb/>
                        gerous</orig>
                  <reg>dangerous</reg>
               </choice> state - she <del/>
               <lb/>
                    is now we trust out of<lb/>
                    absolute danger - But<lb/>
                    still far from safe<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    Your obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">&gt;Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p><!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. --></p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
            <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
            <closer><!--Use the <closer> element again to hold Address Leaf information.-->
               <address>
                        <!--Include any text written on the address leaf; use a separate "addrLine" for each line and indicate line breaks. -->
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
